The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Friday, July 16, 2004  BTC fiasco Hyderabad races 
 FROM WILLIAM TELL				 										Bangalore: Protesting against some tough medication rules, the Bangalore Turf Club (BTC) trainers have refused to declare runners for the weekends races. A meeting between the turf authorities and trainers, on Wednesday, produced no result. Therefore, it is unlikely that races during the weekend will be held in Bangalore.				 										Calcutta: Royal Calcutta Turf Club (RCTC) has decided to conduct inter-state betting on Hyderabad races next Monday and also on July 26, according to an RCTC notification.
